Sentencas: The impedance of anode-supported single cells [Ni/8 yttria-stabilized zirconia (YSZ) anode; La0.58Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-delta cathode; 8YSZ electrolyte; area 1 cm(2)] was characterized in a broad measuring range of temperature and air/fuel gas composition.
Titulo: Evaluation and modeling of the cell resistance in anode-supported solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The data has been analyzed by calculating the distribution function of relaxation times (DRTs).

Sentencas: DRT computations enabled us to separate five different loss mechanisms occurring inside the cathode and anode without the need of an equivalent circuit.
Titulo: Evaluation and modeling of the cell resistance in anode-supported solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Two processes exhibit a systematic dependency on changes in the oxygen partial pressure of the cathode gas and thus can be attributed to diffusional and electrochemical losses on the cathode side.
Titulo: Evaluation and modeling of the cell resistance in anode-supported solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The remaining three processes are very sensitive to changes in the fuel gas but are not affected by variations of the cathode gas.
Titulo: Evaluation and modeling of the cell resistance in anode-supported solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: These resistances are classified as a gas diffusion polarization within the anode-substrate and as an electro-oxidation reaction at the triple-phase boundary, respectively.
